{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb79fe86a-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s421"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"421"},"text":"§ 421.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Additional provisions with respect to the Department of Energy","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb79fe86b-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s421/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Authority To Prohibit Access to Certain Materials","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of Energy may prohibit the Inspector General of the Department of Energy from accessing Restricted Data and nuclear safeguards information protected from disclosure under chapter 12 of the Atomic Energy Act of 1954 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2161"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 2161","children":[],"tail":" et seq.) and intelligence or counterintelligence, as defined in section 3 of the National Security Act of 1947 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s3003"},"text":"50 U.S.C. 3003","children":[],"tail":"), if the Secretary of Energy determines that the prohibition is necessary to protect the national security or prevent the significant impairment to the national security interests of the United States."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb79fe86c-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s421/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Notification to Inspector General and Statement to Congress","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 7 days after the date on which the Secretary of Energy exercises any power authorized under subsection (a), the Secretary shall notify the Inspector General of the Department of Energy in writing of the reasons for such exercise. Within 30 days after receipt of any such notice, the Inspector General of the Department of Energy shall submit to the appropriate committees of Congress a statement concerning such exercise.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb79fe86d-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286/s3/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–286, § 3(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/4252"},"text":"136 Stat. 4252","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb79fe86e-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"prospectiveAmendment","id":"idb79fe86f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments Not Shown in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section was derived from section 8N of the Inspector General Act of 1978, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/452"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–452","children":[],"tail":", which was set out in the former Appendix to this title, and as it existed as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-10-19"},"text":"Oct. 19, 2021","children":[],"tail":". "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/452/s8N"},"text":"Section 8N of Pub. L. 95–452","children":[],"tail":" was amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/dE/tLII/s5272/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, div. E, title LII, § 5272(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/3241"},"text":"136 Stat. 3241","children":[],"tail":", prior to being repealed and reenacted as this section by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–286","children":[],"tail":", §§ 3(b), 7, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/4252"},"text":"136 Stat. 4252","children":[],"tail":", 4361. For applicability of those amendments to this section, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/286/s5/b"},"text":"section 5(b) of Pub. L. 117–286","children":[],"tail":", set out in a Transitional and Savings Provisions note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":". "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/452/s8N"},"text":"Section 8N of Pub. L. 95–452","children":[],"tail":" was amended in subsection (b) by striking “committees of Congress” and inserting “congressional committees”. For definition of “appropriate congressional committees”, which would result from application of the amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263","children":[],"tail":", see Amendments Not Shown in Text note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s401"},"text":"section 401 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb79fe870-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idb79fe871-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attr